Are two numbers the same?


################### BITWISE OPERATOR ################
1) bitwise AND (&)
2) bitwise OR (|)
3) bitwise XOR ( cap symbol cntrl pinadi)
4) right shift (>>)
5) left shift (<<)
bitwise AND.
It is denoted by the single ampersand sign (&). This operator takes two numbers as operands and does AND operation 
on every bit of two numbers. here and logic is applicable t t (t);  f f(f) ; 0 =false 1 = true
12 =00001100 (In Binary)                      0 0 0 0 1 1 0 0
25 =00011001 (In Binary)					  0 0 0 1 1 0 0 1
											____________________
											  0 0 0 0 1 0 0 0 = 8 (In Decimal)


